SIM_TIME

public static int SIM_TIME
Defines the maximum time of simulation.

MAX_NODE

public static int MAX_NODE
Defines the ID space or maximum number of peers in the system.

SCENARIO_FILE

public static java.lang.String SCENARIO_FILE
Defines the name of scenario file.

SYNC_UPDATE

public static boolean SYNC_UPDATE
Enables/disables the synchronous update feature of simulator. If this variable is true the simulator calls the syncMethod of all peers in system at each time unit.

MONITOR

public static boolean MONITOR
Enabling/Disabling the Monitor is controlled by this variable.

SKEWED

public static boolean SKEWED
The peer IDs in ID space can be distributed uniformly or it can be skewed. If this variable is true then the distribution of IDs are skewed.

NUM_OF_CLUSTER

public static int NUM_OF_CLUSTER
In case of having skewed ID distribution, this variable shows the number of clusters in ID space.

PROB_OF_CLUSTER

public static double PROB_OF_CLUSTER
Defines the percentage of peers that are places in clusters. For example if NUM OF CLUSTER is 4 and PROB OF CLUSTER is 0.7, means there are 4 clusters in ID space and 70% of whole peers are placed in these clusters.

NETWORK_LATENCY

public static int NETWORK_LATENCY
Each message from one peer to other peers passes through the core network. This variable defines the mean latency in the core network.

NETWORK_LATENCY_DRIFT

public static int NETWORK_LATENCY_DRIFT
To have a realistic model of latency, SICSIM assumes the latency between each two peers in not fixed and changes in time. This variable shows the maximum latency drift that each connection has.

LINK_LATENCY

public static int LINK_LATENCY
Defines the maximum link latency of links in the system.

FAILURE_DETECTOR_LATENCY

public static int FAILURE_DETECTOR_LATENCY
In case of failing a peer, the peers who registered for this peer, will receive the failure notification of failed peer in maximum FAILURE DETECTOR LATENCY time unit.

public static int FAILURE_DETECTOR_MAX_TIME

LOG_SIM

public static boolean LOG_SIM
Printing out the debugging information of simulator core is enabled/disabled by this variable.

LOG_LEVEL

public static int LOG_LEVEL
Defines the level of printing debugging information. 0 means disable, 1 means error, 2 means warning, 3 means notice, 4 means info and 5 means debug. If it sets to 5, every debugging messages of SICSIM core is printed, but if it sets to 3, only notice messages are printed, and setting it to 0, disable the printing debug information.
